mlx-lama-swift
==============

From-scratch MLX-Swift architecture ports (no pre-existing MLX implementations) of two
inpainting / object-removal models, for the MLXEngine `imageInpaint` capability (Forge "Erase"):

  LaMa (Big-LaMa) — Copyright (c) Samsung Research — Apache License 2.0
  https://github.com/advimman/lama
  "Resolution-robust Large Mask Inpainting with Fourier Convolutions" (WACV 2022)
  The Fast Fourier Convolution originates from https://github.com/pkumivision/FFC (NeurIPS 2020).

  MI-GAN — Copyright (c) Picsart AI Research (PAIR) — MIT License
  https://github.com/Picsart-AI-Research/MI-GAN
  "MI-GAN: A Simple Baseline for Image Inpainting on Mobile Devices" (ICCV 2023)

The Swift/MLX ports (`Sources/{LaMa,MIGAN,MLXInpaint}`) are original to this repository and
licensed MIT (see LICENSE). The LaMa architecture + weights remain Apache-2.0; MI-GAN MIT.

Converted MLX weights (fp16) are published to Hugging Face mlx-community:
  - mlx-community/LaMa-bf16                  (Apache-2.0)
  - mlx-community/MI-GAN-512-places2-fp16    (MIT)
  - mlx-community/MI-GAN-256-places2-fp16    (MIT)
  - mlx-community/MI-GAN-256-ffhq-fp16       (MIT)
Collection: https://huggingface.co/collections/mlx-community/inpainting-mlx

Two-layer license declaration for MLXEngine admission (C7/C8):
  weight license = Apache-2.0 (LaMa) / MIT (MI-GAN)   ·   port-code license = MIT.
